//! Preprocessed columns for the prover.
//!
//! Preprocessed tables are constant lookup tables that don't depend on execution.
//! They are generated once and committed first in the proving process.
//!
//! # Architecture
//!
//! The preprocessed infrastructure is generated by the `relations!` macro:
//! - `PreprocessedTable` trait: Defines table structure and index computation
//! - `Counter<T>`: Tracks multiplicities during opcode trace generation
//! - `PreProcessedTrace`: Aggregates all preprocessed column data
//! - `Counters`: Aggregates all multiplicity counters
//!
//! # Adding a new preprocessed table
//!
//! 1. Create a module `new_table.rs` with `pub struct Table;`
//! 2. Implement `PreprocessedTable` trait for it
//! 3. Add `new_table: col1, col2;` to the `preprocessed` section in `relations!`

